gov.nasa.jpf.listener

Class DeadlockAnalyzer

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpf.ListenerAdapter
      • gov.nasa.jpf.listener.DeadlockAnalyzer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JPFListener, PublisherExtension, SearchListener, VMListener

    public class DeadlockAnalyzer
extends ListenerAdapter
    example of a listener that creates property specific traces. The interesting thing is that it does so without the need to store steps, i.e. it maintains it's own transition stack. this is still work in progress, analyzing the trace can be much more elaborate (we just dump up to a max history size for now) <2do> DeadlockAnalyzer output can be confusing if a reorganizing ThreadList is used (which reassigns thread ids)
